pan class=\"t_tag in 2008 \" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%D6%D0%B9%FA\">China</span>4G, its network transmission The speed can reach 2G per second, which is equivalent to one second in the next movie. In the Japanese and Korean movies of the end of the 90s of the last century, such as \"My Sassy Girlfriend,\" the heroine used the video that allows the other party to see her <span class=\"t_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http:/ /mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%B5%E7%BB%B0\">Phone</span> is one of the important applications of 3G technology. The use of 3G in countries such as Japan and South Korea was the end of the last century. At present, some regions in foreign countries have already tried to run 3.5G or even 4G networks. <br />\n</font><br />\n<font color=\"black\"> </font><font color=\"black\">(The following is misleading) The main difference between the third generation (3G) and the first two generations that came out in 2009 is the speed at which sound and data are transmitted. The upgrade, it can achieve seamless roaming on a global scale, and deal with a variety of media formats such as images, music, video streaming, etc., providing a variety of information services including web browsing, conference calls, e-commerce, etc. Consider good compatibility with existing second generation systems. In order to provide this service, the wireless network must be able to support different data transmission speeds, that is, to support at least 2 Mbps (megabits per second) and 384 kbps (kilobits per second) in indoor, outdoor, and driving environments. And a transmission speed of 144 kbps. (This value will vary depending on the network environment). <br />\n</font><br />\n<font color=\"black\"> The 3G standard, the International Telecommunication Union (ITU) currently determines the world\'s four major 3G standards, which are WCDMA, CDMA2000 and TD-SCDMA and WiMAX. </font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\">The 3G standard International Telecommunication Union (ITU) identified four major wireless interface standards for W-CDMA, CDMA2000, TD-SCDMA and WiMAX in May 2000, and wrote the 3G technical guidance document \"2000\". International Mobile Communications Plan (IMT&mdash; 2000). CDMA is the abbreviation of Code Division Multiple Access and is the technical basis of the third generation mobile communication system. The first generation of mobile communication systems used frequency division multiple access (FDMA) analog modulation. The main disadvantages of this system are low spectrum utilization and signalling interference voice services. The second generation mobile communication system mainly adopts the time division multiple access (TDMA) digital modulation method, which improves the system capacity and uses independent channel to transmit signaling, which greatly improves the system performance, but the system capacity of TDMA is still limited, and the handover performance is still limited. Still not perfect. The CDMA system shows great development potential due to its simple frequency planning, large system capacity, high frequency reuse coefficient, strong multipath resistance, good communication quality, soft capacity and soft switching. Here are some of the 3G standards:<br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> </font><br />\n<font color=\"black\">(1) W-CDMA</font><font color=\"black\"><br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> Also known as WCDMA, the full name is Wideband CDMA, also known as CDMA Direct Spread, which means wideband coded multiple access, which is based on the 3G technical specification developed by the GSM network. Wideband CDMA technology, which is basically the same as the wideband CDMA technology proposed by Japan, is currently being further integrated. W-CDMA supporters are mainly European manufacturers based on the GSM system, and Japanese companies are more or less involved, including Ericsson, Alcatel, <span class=\"t_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" Href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%C5%B5%BB%F9%D1%C7\">Nokia</span>, Lucent, Nortel, and NTT in Japan , Fujitsu, Sharp and other manufacturers. The standard proposes an evolution strategy for GSM (2G)-GPRS-EDGE-WCDMA (3G). The system can be installed on existing GSM networks, making it easier for system providers to transition, but the acceptance of this new technology in Asia, where the GSM system is quite popular, is expected to be quite high. Therefore, W-CDMA has an innate market advantage. <br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> </font><br />\n<font color=\"black\">(2)CDMA2000</font><font color=\"black\"><br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> CDMA2000 is a broadband CDMA technology developed by narrowband CDMA (CDMA IS95) technology, also known as CDMA Multi-Carrier, which is led by Qualcomm North America, <span class=\" T_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%C4%A6%CD%D0%C2%DE%C0%AD\">Motorola </span>, Lucent and Samsung, which joined later, all participated, and Korea is now the leader of the standard. The system is derived from the narrowband CDMAOne digital standard and can be upgraded directly from the original CDMAOne architecture to 3G with low construction costs. However, the current regions using CDMA are only Japan, South Korea and North America, so CDMA2000 supporters are not as good as W-CDMA. However, CDMA2000\'s R&D technology is currently the fastest among all standards, and many 3G mobile phones have already taken the lead. The standard proposes an evolution strategy from CDMA IS95(2G)-CDMA20001x-CDMA20003x(3G). CDMA2000 1x is known as the 2.5 generation mobile communication technology. The main difference between CDMA20003x and CDMA20001x is the application of multi-carrier technology to increase the bandwidth by using three carriers. Currently <span class=\"t_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%D6%D0%B9%FA%B5%E7% D0%C5\">China Telecom</span> is using this solution to transition to 3G and has built a CDMA IS95 network. <br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> </font><br />\n<font color=\"black\">(3)TD-SCDMA</font><font color=\"black\"><br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> Full name Time Division - Synchronous CDMA (Time <span class=\"t_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php ?name=%CD%AC%B2%BD\">Sync</span> CDMA), the standard is a 3G standard independently developed by mainland China, June 29, 1999, China Institute of Telecommunications Science and Technology of the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications ( Datang Telecom) proposed to the ITU. The standard will be Smart Wireless, <span class=\"t_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%CD%AC%B2%BD \">Sync</span> CDMA and <span class=\"t_tag\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\" href=\"http://mbbs.enet.com.cn/tag.php?name=%C8%ED% Today\'s leading international technologies such as BC%FE\">Software</span> radios combine to provide unique advantages in spectrum utilization, flexibility in business support, frequency flexibility and cost. In addition, due to the huge market in China, the standard has been valued by major telecom equipment manufacturers, and more than half of the world\'s equipment manufacturers have announced that they can support the TD&mdash; SCDMA standard. The standard proposes a transition to 3G without the intermediate link of 2.5 generations, which is very suitable for the GSM system to upgrade to 3G. <br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> </font><br />\n<font color=\"black\">(4)WiMAX</font><font color=\"black\"><br />\n</font><br />\n<br />\n<font color=\"black\"> The full name of WiMAX is Worldwide Interoperability for Microwave Access, also known as 802&middot; 16 wireless metropolitan area network, which is another way for businesses and home users. One mile & quot; broadband wireless connectivity solution. Combining this technology with microwave equipment that requires authorization or exemption will increase the broadband wireless market and improve the awareness of enterprises and service providers due to lower costs. On October 19, 2007, at the International Telecommunications Union\'s wireless communications plenary meeting in Geneva, after most countries voted, WiMAX was officially approved as the fourth global 3G standard after WCDMA, CDMA2000 and TD-SCDMA. </font></div>\n</p>','','','',0,1,1242580013,'',0,'http://',NULL),(36,13,'What brand of propolis is good?','','','','',0,1,1292291460,'',0,'http://www.xxx.com',NULL),(37,13,'Does protein powder have side effects?','','','','',0,1,1292291484,'',0,'http://www.xxx.com',NULL),(38,13,'Vitamin C - vitamins that must be replenished in spring','','','','',0,1,1292291503,'',0,'http://www.xxx.com',NULL),(39,13,'Adolescent smoking can cause depression','','','','',0,1,1292291534,'',0,'http://www.xxx.com',NULL),(40,13,'Frequent eating spicy hot pot affects hair growth and easily causes hair loss','','','','',0,1,1292291558,'',0,'http://www.xxx.com',NULL),(41,13,'Cycling for 5 hours a week or damaging male fertility','','','','',0,1,1292291583,'',0,'http://',NULL),(42,8,'Exchange process','','','','',0,1,1292315950,'',0,'http://',NULL),(43,5,'Evaluasi produk','','','','',0,0,1292315998,'',0,'http://',NULL),(45,7,'Status pemesanan','','','','',0,1,1292316056,'',0,'http://',NULL),(46,10,'Daftar Member Baru','','','','',0,1,1292316080,'',0,'user.php?act=register',NULL),(47,9,'Informasi kontak','','','','',0,0,1292316101,'',0,'http://',NULL),(61,12,'Buy famous perfume to send Bobley fragrance','','','','',0,1,1313660801,'',0,'http://',NULL),(62,12,'Buy home care products to send P&G charm','','','','',0,1,1313660809,'',0,'http://',NULL),(63,12,'Facial care full of 157 yuan home','','','','',0,1,1313660816,'',0,'http://',NULL),(94,18,'Takeaway O2O: Light mode, heavy mode, third party platform'